President of Walker & Dunlop (NYSE:WD), Smith Howard W Iii, sells 19,897 shares worth $577,023
According to Walker & Dunlop's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated Nov 15 04:30 PM, company President, Smith Howard W Iii disclosed selling 19,897 shares at a cost of $29.00. At the time of this transaction (Nov 14), this trade was worth $577,023 in total. As of Nov 14, Smith Howard W Iii now owns 831,849 shares in total worth about $24,123,621.0. 
For the last few recent trades made by Walker & Dunlop (NYSE:WD) President, Smith Howard W Iii, we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: Nov 10: Sold 4,273 shares at the rate of $28.02 per share. Total worth of this trade was $119,731. Total number of shares owned as of Nov 10 were 944,076
SEC Form 4 filing: Nov 11: Sold 92,330 shares at the rate of $28.55 per share. Total worth of this trade was $2,635,735. Total number of shares owned as of Nov 11 were 851,746
SEC Form 4 filing: Nov 08: Sold 7,000 shares at the rate of $28.02 per share. Total worth of this trade was $196,118. Total number of shares owned as of Nov 08 were 970,105




